com.estimote.coresdk.recognition.packets

Class ConfigurableDevice

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.estimote.coresdk.recognition.packets.Packet
      • com.estimote.coresdk.recognition.packets.ConfigurableDevice
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable

    public class ConfigurableDevice
extends Packet
    General object for all connectivity packets advertised by Estimote's devices. You need to obtain them in order to establish connection to your owned devices. The best way to do this is to enable BeaconManager.startConfigurableDevicesDiscovery(). Scanned objects will be passed to the listener interface - BeaconManager.ConfigurableDevicesListener.
    Author:
    Pawel Dylag (pawel.dylag@estimote.com)

    • Field Detail

      • type

        public final DeviceType type
        Configurable device object is a general concept for all connectivity packets that our device's advertise. To verify the kind of a device (location beacon, proximity beacon, nearable, mirror, etc.) you can use this field with enum type

      • deviceId

        public final DeviceId deviceId
        Id of device that is broadcasting this packet.

      • macAddress

        public final MacAddress macAddress
        Mac address of device. Notice that Nearable devices are rotating their Mac addresses, so you better don't rely on them

      • appVersion

        public final java.lang.String appVersion
        String with encoded SemVer of device's firmware version (application)

      • bootloaderVersion

        public final java.lang.String bootloaderVersion
        String with encoded SemVer of device's firmware versin (bootloader)

      • isShaken

        public final boolean isShaken
        This field will be set to true, if device is being shaken. This option needs to be enabled on beacon (Shake to connect)

      • isClose

        public final boolean isClose
        Near to connect field - is set to true if device is cloe to the user's phone. This feature needs to be enabled prior tu use it

      • rssi

        public final java.lang.Integer rssi
        Received Signal Strength Indicator of given packet. This value may be affected by some of our smoothing algorithms

      • txPower

        public final java.lang.Integer txPower
        Transfer power of given packet. In decibels

      • discoveryTime

        public final java.lang.Long discoveryTime
        Exact time when this packet was scanned
